A workflow orchestrates several activities. The parent workflow is started with priority_key=2. One activity is explicitly started with priority_key=4 (lower priority). A second activity is started without any explicit priority setting. An engineer wants to understand how the second activity's task will be dispatched relative to other tasks in the queue. What priority will the second activity's task have?

```go
workflowOptions := client.StartWorkflowOptions{
    ID:        "orchestrator-id",
    TaskQueue: "work-queue",
    Priority:  temporal.Priority{PriorityKey: 2},
}
// Inside the workflow:
ao1 := workflow.ActivityOptions{
    StartToCloseTimeout: time.Minute,
    Priority:            temporal.Priority{PriorityKey: 4},
}
ao2 := workflow.ActivityOptions{
    StartToCloseTimeout: time.Minute,
    // No Priority set
}
err1 := workflow.ExecuteActivity(workflow.WithActivityOptions(ctx, ao1), ActivityOne).Get(ctx, nil)
err2 := workflow.ExecuteActivity(workflow.WithActivityOptions(ctx, ao2), ActivityTwo).Get(ctx, nil)
```
